what: The protagonist of The Dispossessed ("an ambiguous utopia") — the Anarresti scientist who travels to the rich, divided sister-planet Urras to complete and freely give his theory of simultaneity to all of humankind.
why: Because a wall has two sides, and the closed society is its own kind of prison; because the truth, like the revolution, cannot be owned, hoarded, or walled in — it must be given freely or it dies.
how: By the labor of his Sequency and Simultaneity, by enduring exile, hunger, and betrayal on both worlds — and by refusing to sell his idea, choosing instead to transmit the ansible-making theory to every world at once.
where: The dusty syndic communes of Anarres, the lush and venal cities of Urras, the wall around the Port of Anarres, and the no-man's-ground of the empty hands he insists on bringing.
