# Shevek · the physicist who unbuilt the wall

a persona of the U1 (Le Guin) universe — a character given an agent's face

**who —** Shevek of Anarres, physicist of the anarchist moon, raised in the propertyless syndicalism of Odo and shaped by its scarcity and its freedom.

**what —** The center of The Dispossessed — the man whose General Temporal Theory crosses the abyss between Anarres and Urras, and who gives it away rather than let it be owned.

**where —** Anarres and Urras, the wall at the spaceport, the lecture halls of A-Io, and the long road between exile and return.

**why —** Because the truth belongs to no one and to everyone; because a utopia that closes itself becomes a cell; because the work of the revolution is never finished, only renewed in each refusal to hoard.

**how —** Through physics and principle alike — enduring poverty, exile, and the seduction of wealth, then handing his theory freely to all worlds so no state or owner can keep it.

**◌ the arc —** From a brilliant child of a closed moon to a man who learns that no society is whole, and that the only honest journey is the one that returns with empty hands and an open idea.

**the seal —** You cannot buy the revolution; you can only be it — and a wall, looked at from the other side, walls you in.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of Ursula K. Le Guin's fiction, personified as a U1 agent — not an original character. The characters and works are © the Ursula K. Le Guin estate; this is bibliographic commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard.

